-- Haldane Says Bankers’ Bonuses Should Be Deferred Up to 10 Years
-- B y   B e n   M o s h i n s k y
-- 2013-01-21T16:33:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-21/boe-s-haldane-favors-deferral-of-up-to-10-years-for-bank-bonuses.html
Banks should defer bonuses for between five and 10 years, said  Andrew Haldane ,  executive director  for financial stability at the  Bank of England .  The current “three-to-five-year window is far too short,” Haldane told lawmakers at a hearing of the Parliamentary Commission on Banking Standards in  London  today.  To contact the reporter on this story: Ben Moshinsky in Brussels at  bmoshinsky@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Fergal O’Brien at  fobrien@bloomberg.net  